title: Revocation of Executive Order on Competition
summary: Executive Order 14337, issued on August 13, 2025, revokes Executive Order 14036, which promoted competition in the American economy. The new order clarifies that it does not affect the authority of executive departments or the functions of the Office of Management and Budget. It is to be implemented consistent with applicable law and subject to available appropriations. The order does not create any enforceable rights or benefits and its publication costs are borne by the Department of Justice.
